 <item> <title>Giving Back to Students</title>
 <link>https://www.ed.gov/content/giving-back-students</link>
 <description>Today, as hardworking Americans across the country file their taxes or await their return, middle class families and students paying for college loans will find a larger refund coming their way.  The American Opportunity Tax Credit alleviates up to $2,500 of federal income tax owed for individuals paying for college loans and making up to $90,000 a year or for couples making up to $180,000.</description>
